R1- If measuredTemp>refTemp → contReg=2 →  On the 7-segment display H →  Turn on PORTC.2, which is connected to an LED ONLY
R2- If measuredTemp<refTemp → contReg=1 →  On the 7-segment display C →  Turn on PORTC.1, which is connected to an LED ONLY
R3- If measuredTemp=refTemp → contReg=0 →  display nothing

Other system requirements include the following: 
R4- The refTemp can be between +10 Degree celsius and +50 Degree celsius. 
R5- The measuredTemp can be between -20 Degree celsius and +60 Degree celsius. 
R6- You can only use PORTC. No other ports can be used as output.
R7- Your program must start from register 0x8 in the program memory. 
R8- Make sure the following variables are in the following register locations: 
	refTemp→ REG 0x20, measuredTemp→ REG 0x21, contReg → REG 0x22

//-----------------------------
// Title: ?
//-----------------------------
// Purpose: what does this program do? 
// Dependencies: Are you using any header files - if no say NONE
// Compiler: Which IDE Simulator Version ???
// Author: Your name 
// OUTPUTS: outputs of this program? What are they connected to? 
// INPUTS: inputs of this program? What are they connected to? 
// Versions:
//  	V1.0: today’s date - First version 
//  	V1.2: date - Changes something….
//-----------------------------

	ORG 0x08 ;starts program ar 0x08 (R7)

	;set register locations (R8)
	refTemp EQU 0x20
	measuredTemp EQU 0x21
	contReg EQU 0x22


	;arbituary values for inputs
	input_measuredTemp EQU 0x05
	input_refTemp EQU 0xA



	MOVLW input_refTemp
	MOVWF refTemp
	MOVLW input_measuredTemp
	MOVWF measuredTemp


	;if measuredTemp = refTemp, contReg = 0
	MOVFW refTemp
	CPFSEQ  measuredTemp, W	;Compare F with W, skip if F = W
	GOTO check_less_or_greater
	SLEEP

check_less_or_greater:
	;measuredTemp<refTemp → contReg=1
	INCF contReg, 0x01
	CPFSLT  measuredTemp, W	;Compare F with W, skip if F < W
	GOTO check_if_greater
	SLEEP

check_if_greater:
	;measuredTemp>refTemp → contReg=2
	INCF contReg,0x01
	CPFSGT  measuredTemp, W	;Compare F with W, skip if F > W
	ADDLW 0x11
	SLEEP



